<TITLE> Bashundhara man refused bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 17 (bdnews24.com)  A Bashundhara Group official, rounded up from Gazipur on May 14 on various charges including trespassing on government property, was refused bail on Monday. Masum Hossain, a senior administrative officer of Bashundhara's Mouchak City Housing Project was arrested from Madhyaparha area under Kaliakair upazila of Gazipur. Senior Judicial Magistrate Sheikh Taique Aziz refused the bail petition filed by the defendant's lawyer Sudip Kumar Chakrabarti, general recording officer of the court police, sub inspector Rabiul Islam told bdnews24.com. Mohammed Mokhlesur Rahman, assistant land officer of Shafipur union, filed two cases on May 13, against Bashundhara Group chairman Ahmed Akbar Sobhan, popularly known as Shah Alam. The cases also charged another 40-50 unidentified people. b
